Gave this another go after finding it a little 🥱 a few years ago…my impression is slightly improved: it’s obviously a well shot, at times compelling movie but eventually, one just can’t be bothered can they? Nobody is all that charming and the most compelling performance, sorry to say, is when tilda swinton says “the worst” and then leans against the wall

Determined to be a Harris Dickinson fangirl so watched this in the Uber home

This should have done everything for me but instead it just annoyed me!

This 100% did it for me! The writing wasn’t super strong so the more intense life stuff was a bit saggy and robotic but really strong performances and a real sense of sibling solidarity sold it for me. Also uses music really well. And I got my wish—I cried.
I cannot get sick of it! I could watch this weekly
